x="975" y="450" width="60" height="30" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="l4ohZ6PaDyAUnrVgu7BD-56" value="<p data-end="671" data-start="223"><font style="font-size: 14px;">The Foundation’s first priority is to <strong data-end="271" data-start="261">secure</strong> anomalous entities, objects, and phenomena before they can threaten the public. This involves identifying potential anomalies, isolating them from civilian exposure, and ensuring they are recovered with minimal disruption. Security teams operate worldwide to intercept anomalies, erase evidence, and maintain secrecy, ensuring that the public remains unaware of the dangers lurking in the shadows.</font></p>" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;movable=0;resizable=0;rotatable=0;deletable=0;editable=0;locked=1;connectable=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry y="510" width="310" height="190" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="l4ohZ6PaDyAUnrVgu7BD-57" value="<p data-end="671" data-start="223"><font style="font-size: 14px;">Once secured, anomalies must be <strong style="" data-end="744" data-start="731">contained</strong> to prevent further harm. Containment procedures are carefully designed for each individual anomaly, ranging from simple storage in a locked vault to elaborate, custom-built containment chambers. Foundation scientists, engineers, and security personnel work together to establish safe, reliable measures that keep anomalies isolated and under constant surveillance. Containment ensures that the unpredictable nature of anomalies is controlled, minimizing risks to personnel and the outside world.</font></p>" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;movable=0;resizable=0;rotatable=0;deletable=0;editable=0;locked=1;connectable=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="425" y="510" width="310" height="190" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="l4ohZ6PaDyAUnrVgu7BD-58" value="<p data-end="671" data-start="223"><font style="font-size: 14px;">The ultimate mission of the Foundation is to <strong data-end="1326" data-start="1315">protect</strong> humanity. By securing and containing anomalies, the Foundation shields the public from knowledge and exposure that could cause panic or chaos. Protection also extends to anomalies themselves, preserving them for research and study, and ensuring they are not exploited by hostile groups or governments. The Foundation protects not only the world from the anomalies, but also the anomalies from the world.</font></p>"
